  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: Geth\nVersion: 1.4.5-stable-a269a713\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.5.1\nOS: linux\n\nWhen I receive a block notification (via filter polling) I've called eth_getTransactionByHash ( web3.js getTransaction() ) for each transaction hash.\nIn the middle I call eth_blockNumber ( web3.js [getBlockNumber()](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JavaScript-API#web3ethblocknumber) ) to calculate the confirmations number.\n\nHere's the pseudo-code:\n\n``` javascript\nweb3.eth = Promise.promisifyAll(web3.eth);\n\nconst tx = yield web3.eth.getTransactionAsync('0x123');\n\nlet confirmations  = 0;\n\nif (tx.blockNumber !== null) {\n  const blockNumber = yield web3.eth.getBlockNumberAsync();\n  confirmations  = blockNumber - tx.blockNumber + 1;\n}\n```\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nThe variable **confirmations** is greater or equal than 0 for every confirmed transaction. \n#### Actual behaviour\n\nThe variable **confirmations** in some point returns **-1**. \nMaybe eth_blocknumber call is out of sync?\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nI can't reproduce this problem, it just happens sometimes.\n#### Backtrace\n\nNot available.\n",
